deck:
The boss of West Demon World, and best friend and rival to Staz.
He is a half-bread werewolf, and was abounded by his father; Wolf Daddy, the king of Demon World.
description:
Wolf is the son of the Demon World's king; Wolf Daddy, but he was kicked out of his royal family at a early age, because he was a half-bread. Wolf then made a life in the Lower Demon World where he started a gang of his own.

One day, a vampire child by the name Staz felt down from the sky. He told Wolf that he wanted to go to the Human World, so Wolf, eager after a fight with a noble demon, told him that he would give him money, if he could defeat him in combat. But as they fight, Wolf notice that Staz didn't put up a fight at all. Angrily, Wolf demanded to know why, to witch Staz says that if he actually fought Wolf, he might kill him. Wolf realized he is right, and they became best friends and rivals.

As a teenager, Wolf is the boss of the West Demon World. He has used the most of his life to fight other gangs and make his territory grow(he has control over 18 out of 21 districts in the West), so that he one day may be strong enough to defeat his rival and friend Staz, who are also a territory boss himself. Taking over all of the territories in the Lower Demon World would also mean that he could take his rightful place among the elite-class demons, but he honestly doesn't think too much about that.

He one day gets a visit from Staz, who ask Wolf if he can get him the "Book Of Human Resurrection" that can be found in his territory, but even though Wolf is Staz friend, just giving the book away is not a option for a territory boss. Staz proposes that they have a competition. If Staz win, Wolf will get him the book. But if Wolf win, he gets Fuyumi. Since Wolf finds Fuyumi very attractive (even though he claims that she is not his type) he accepts. The competition was suppose to be bowling, but Bell Hydra warns Wolf that Staz would cheat, and suggest that he tricks Staz into a boxing match instead, witch he does.

In the boxing match, Wolf has the obvious advantage with his werewolf strength, and because of the ring, Staz has no roam to concentrate, and can therefor not use his magic on Wolf. But Staz succeed getting the upper hand by draining Wolf for magic. But the fight almost ends badly, when Wolf starts insulting Staz, witch enrage Staz to the point that he attempts to use his magic to crush Wolf's heart. Staz is luckily stopped by Fuyumi, and the match ends without a winner. But Staz gets the book anyway, since it was never to be found in Wolf's territory. Bell had it all along, and just wanted to test Staz, and gives it to him.

Staz travels to Acropolis to find the author to the book, and leaves Fuyumi under Wolf's protection. But it is soon shown that Fuyumi is slowly starting to fade. After Wolf takes her to Franken Stein, a demon doctor, it is revealed that she is no longer capable of absorbing magic from the Demon World's atmosphere now that she has fed on Staz's blood, and without magic, she will seize to exist.

Bell appears in Franken's lab and reveals to Wolf that Franken wants to use Fuyumi to destroy a failed experiment named Papradon Akim, a monster created by body-parts from other demons. The monster has run amok, looking for better body-parts from other demons. Wolf makes a deal with Franken that he will cure Fuyumi, if he destroys Papradon.

Wolf finds and fight the monstrosity, but he is no match to Papradon, and must transform into his wolf-form. this is in the end not enough, and he must revert back to normal. Luckily, Staz return in time to take over the fight, while Wolf restore his magic. When Wolf comes back to help Staz, he sees that Staz has already destroyed the creature, and challenge the now stronger than ever Staz to combat, only to be defeated. Wolf knows that Staz even held back, and swears that he will one day force Staz to use his full strength.

One day, Wolf reserves a letter from Wolf Daddy(the first contact he had with his father since the day he abandoned him) that says that he have to go to the Human World and fetch his mother Katy(or else!). The letter also has passport and money, that allow Wolf to travel to the Human World. Wolf has no interest in running errands for Wolf Daddy, but decides to go anyway, so he can meet his mother.

Despite a very old, and close to useless photography, Wolf manege to find Katy, since he could recognize his eyes on her. He tells her that Wolf Daddy has asked for her to come back to the Demon World. She tells Wolf that it is no use, since she has used up all her magic to stay alive in the Human World, but that Wolf might have inherited her magic, and offer him to teach him how to use it, if he will go in her place to Wolf Daddy.

Powers & Abilities

Wolf can use his magic to increase his strength, witch makes him stronger than any lower class demons.

He can also use his magic to turn into werewolf form, witch makes him even stronger, and also grants him claws that can cut through anything and create shock-waves. But being a half-bread, he can only stay in this for for 3 minutes.

Wolf is also a formidable combatant, with years of experience at street-smart combat.

He also has some degree of swordsmanship by the use of a iron pipe.

Weapons and Equipment

Wolf's signature weapon is his iron pipe. He can seal some of his magic inside the pipe, and that way make it work as a extension of his body.
name: Wolf

deck: The father of Kirk Langstrom, aka Man-Bat.
description:
History

Abraham Langstrom was the father of Kirk Langstrom and a powerful business figure in Gotham where he rose to power as a corporate raider. This would see him prey on other companies that he bought and divided in order to make his fortune. He would be the head of Patriarch Biopharmaceuticals and a corporate rival of Thomas Wayne. During these years, he held nothing but disappointment for his son who he felt was weak willed. Despite his competition with Thomas Wayne, Abraham held an admiration for his son Bruce Wayne who he felt shared many ideals as the older Langstrom. At some point, he sold his son's Man-Bat serum to Talia al Ghul in order for her to create her Man-Bat super soldiers. He later refined the serum for himself and transformed himself into Man-Bat where he began terrorizing Gotham with his predatory acts attracting the attention of Batman.
name: Abraham Langstrom

deck: Legendary viking, nicknamed after his special furry pants.
description:
Vikings

Ragnar Lothbrok appears in the television series Vikings as the main protagonist of the show. Ragnar is portrayed by the actor Travis Fimmel and appears in all episodes of the show. Ragnar is the former king of Sweden/Norway and former Jarl of Kattegat. Ragnar is portrayed as a brutal and skillful warrior and a brilliant tactician. Ragnar, even when wounded was able to defeat the earlier Jarl of Kattegat in single combat.

Physical Appearance

In the earlier seasons of the show, Ragnar is seen to have a long ponytail with shaved sides. His eyes often varies color between bright blue and light green. Ragnar is also sporting a long beard, something that seems to be a common thing among the Vikings in the show. Ragnar is a fairly tall man, although compared to many of the other Vikings, he may seem fairly short. Although he may be shorter than most of the other Vikings, he has a very wide, muscular build, which does him great in combat situations.
name: Ragnar Lodbrok
